other_tests.findings: Successful resuscitation from haloperidol-induced cardiac arrest.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Converted to narrow, supraventricular tachycardia within 2 minutes of lipid infusion.

other_tests.date: One hour after the cardiac arrest
other_tests.findings: Sinus tachycardia at 107 beats/min, QT interval of 288 ms, corrected QT interval of 385 ms.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Normalization of QTc was contemporaneous with administration of lipid emulsion and recovery of normal vital signs.

other_tests.findings: Apical akinesis with an ejection fraction of 30% to 35%.
Improved hemodynamic stability and resolved cardiogenic shock.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Normalization of arterial pressure, correction of metabolic acidosis, and resolution of heart failure signs by the next day.
